            h2 Introduction
            +tex.
                $\mathbf{Definition}$ (Isomorphism Introduction).
            +tex(true).
                $$
                    \mathrm{id}_\cong : A\cong A =_{def}
                $$
            +tex(true).
                $$
                    (id(A),id(A),\lambda x.[i]x, \lambda x.[i]x).
                $$
            +code.
                def iso-intro (A: U)
                  : iso A A
                 := ( id A,
                      id A,
                      (\(x:A), <_>x),
                      (\(x:A), <_>x),
                      star
                    )
            br.
            h2 Elimination
            +tex.
                $\mathbf{Definition}$ (Isomorphism Induction Principle).
                For any $C : A \rightarrow B \rightarrow \mathrm{Iso}(A,B)\rightarrow U$
